title: Yreka High VB squad falls to Lassen in 4 sets
text: Yreka High VB squad falls to Lassen in 4 sets Comment   By Daily News staff Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 3:28 PM By Daily News staff Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 3:28 PM SUSANVILLE, Calif. The Yreka High varsity volleyball team fell to Lassen on the road in Northern Athletic League action on Thursday night 18-25, 23-25, 25-21, 22-25. Yreka fell to 14-14 overall and 1-3 in the NAL Lassen improved to 15-7 overall and 4-0 in the NAL. Taylor Callahan had 18 kills and seven blocks for the Lady Miners. Katie Bennett had 33 digs. Gabby Lovelace had 30 digs. Rebekah Kimball finished with 14 service points, while Ashley Cox had 20 assists for Yreka. “Saw some significant improvement in the girls,” Yreka head coach Scott Eastman said. “Still have to work on the little things that add up in the end.” The Yreka JV squad won, while the freshman team lost. Yreka is back home on Tuesday against CentralValley. By Daily News staff   By Daily News staff
